ce:section.ce:para:
To evaluate the blood biocompatibility of the nanoparticles, blood was collected from normal mice, mixed with PBS to a total volume of 5 mL, and centrifuged at 3000 rpm for 5 min. The red blood cells (RBCs) were then washed multiple times with PBS until the supernatant was clear, and diluted with PBS to create a 10-fold dilution. A 0.1 mL aliquot of the RBC solution was mixed with 1 mL of C-dots-T7 dispersions at various concentrations. After incubating the mixtures at 37 °C for 3 h, the samples were centrifuged at 13,000 rpm for 10 min, and the absorbance of the supernatant was measured at 541 nm using a microplate reader. The hemolysis percentage was calculated using the following formula: Hemolysis% = (Ax − Ax0)/(A(+)0 − A(
                        −
                        )0), where Ax is the absorbance of the sample, Ax0 is the intrinsic absorbance of C-dots-T7, A(+)0 is the absorbance of the positive control, and A(
                        −
                        )0 is the absorbance of the negative control [68].
